                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/1765: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-16T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 16, 1934—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Your cables No. 23, March 14, 5 p.m., and No. 24, March 15, 10 a.m.<note
                        n="55" xml:id="d437fn55">Latter not printed.</note> Department considering
                    suggested changes but desires <pb facs="0504" n="438" xml:id="pg_438"/>
                    clarification of specific change for page 8. It is meaningless to insert “and
                    reply brief” after “answer” in the two lines mentioned in your cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
